Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Oxysterlin 1 (cecropin, UCSS1a; natural AMPs; insects, arthropods, invertebrates, animals)

Literature Information.Literature: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals this sequence is most similar (46.7%) toAs-CATH4Mol Wt:  4455.265; GRAVY: -0.48. Active against E. coli (MIC 6.25 uM), E. cloacae clinical isolate (MIC 12.5 uM), S. typhimurium clinical isolate (MIC 6.2 uM), P. aeruginosa ATCC 105663 (MIC 25 uM), S. saprophyticus clinical isolate (MIC 50 uM), and C. parapsilopsis ATCC 22019 (MIC 50 uM).
Literature Information.Author: Toro Segovia LJ, Téllez Ramírez GA, Henao Arias DC, Rivera Duran JD, Bedoya JP, Castaño Osorio JC.2017
Literature Information.Title: Identification and characterization of novel cecropins from the Oxysternon conspicillatum neotropic dung beetle.
